(:Insight {metadata: "{\"trace_ref\":\"71027\",\"tier\":\"mainstream\",\"rationale\":\"Shows specific preference; Detailed description; Recently confirmed; Learned from conversation\",\"proposal_id\":\"6887d3e9-5643-4992-9a80-c6895ca5c807\"}", topic_key: "curator.mainstream", confidence: 1.0, created_at: 2026-04-24T12:43:43.286Z, source_type: "promotion", type: "Insight", created_by: "curator-cli", insight_id: "7e29f2ee-8660-4af9-b9e1-b61ae0f95e5e", version: 1, content: "Team RAM Sprint 9 (P4 — Auto-Curator) complete and merged to main 2026-04-23.

Auto-Curator engine that detects patterns in raw Postgres events and proposes candidate insights WITHOUT writing truth directly to Neo4j or Notion.

Core law: Curator proposes. Paperclip approves. Neo4j remembers. Notion explains.

Pattern detectors:
- detectFailurePatterns — repeated failures (2+ same error, same agent)
- detectWinPatterns — successful patterns (3+ wins of same type)
- detectApprovalPatterns — curator decision patterns (approval rate analysis)
- detectToolRiskPatterns — MCP catalog governance patterns

Dedup/similarity classification:
- >= 0.90 duplicate → reject (suppressed)
- 0.80–0.89 possible supersede → flag for HITL review
- 0.65–0.79 related context → include as reference
- < 0.65 new insight → proceed to scoring

Scoring per candidate:
- confidence (0.0–1.0) from curator scoring heuristics
- impact (low/medium/high)
- frequency (event count)
- novelty_score (similarity to existing)
- reasoning (why this matters)
- tier (emerging/adoption/mainstream)

Governance:
- High-impact ALWAYS requires HITL
- Low-risk = policy-gated auto-approval only
- No direct Neo4j or Notion writes
- All submissions go to canonical_proposals with status='pending'
- auto_curated event type logged to events table

Explainability: every proposal includes source_event_ids, reasoning, and impact assessment.

12/12 tests pass. Commit 32e24cfb.", group_id: "allura-system", observations: [], name: "2b61039d-b79d-492c-aebb-9c4701f73c0e", id: "2b61039d-b79d-492c-aebb-9c4701f73c0e", status: "active"})
